    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Using the <code>-clean</code> option is the way to go, as mentioned by the other answers.</p>\n\n<p>Make sure that you remove it from your <code>.ini</code> or shortcut after you've fixed the problem.  It causes Eclipse to reevaluate all of the plugins everytime it starts and can dramatically increase startup time, depending on how many Eclipse plugins you have installed.</p>\n"
