    "last_activity_date" : 1580375812,
    "creation_date" : 1580375812,
    "answer_id" : 59982541,
    "question_id" : 2030064,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>This will clean the <strong>caches</strong> used to store bundle dependency resolution and eclipse extension registry data. Using this option will force eclipse to <strong>reinitialize these caches</strong>. </p>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Open command prompt (cmd)</li>\n<li>Go to eclipse application location (D:\\eclipse)</li>\n<li>Run command <strong><code>eclipse -clean</code></strong></li>\n</ol>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 6833305,
      "reputation" : 3401,
      "user_id" : 5256337,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/d3GFu.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Lova Chittumuri",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5256337/lova-chittumuri"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 4,
    "last_activity_date" : 1581003439,
    "creation_date" : 1581003439,
    "answer_id" : 60098625,
    "question_id" : 2030064,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Two ways to run eclipse in clean mode.</p>\n\n<p><strong>1 ) In Eclipse.ini file</strong><br></p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Open the eclipse.ini file located in the Eclipse installation directory.<br></li>\n<li>Add -clean first line in the file.<br> </li>\n<li>Save the file.<br></li>\n<li>Restart    Eclipse.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/inMnA.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/inMnA.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n\n<p><strong>2 ) From Command prompt (cmd/command)</strong><br> </p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Go to folder where Eclipse installed.<br></li>\n<li>Take the path of Eclipse  <br> </li>\n<li>C:..\\eclipse\\eclipse.exe -clean<br> </li>\n<li>press enter button <br></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/601fp.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/601fp.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  } ],
